    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName><name ref="Alprandus">Aliprando</name>, habitatore in loco
                                <placeName ref="#places/382">Asilatto</placeName></persName>, filio
                            <persName>quondam <name ref="Lambrandus">Lamprandi</name></persName>,
                        riceve da <persName ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops">Gherardus</persName>
                        gratia Dei huius sancte Lucane ecclesie humilis <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopus</rs> (…) per cartula livellario nomine ad laborandum et
                        gubernandum seu meliorandum (…) id est terra et vinea illa, insimul
                        amembrata in suprascripto loco <placeName ref="#places/382"
                            key="#Confinia #Fiscal_property #Mention">Asilatto</placeName>, prope
                            <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3324" key="#Churches">Sancti
                            Quirici</orgName>, pertinentes ipsius <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                            >episcopatui</rs> vestro <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68"
                            key="#Mother_churches">Sancti Martini</orgName>; et ipsa terra et vinea
                        ego ipse usque modo eas ad manus mea abere videtur; et <rs key="#Confinia"
                            >est tenentes uno caput</rs> in stirpeto, qui fuit <persName
                            key="#Confinia"><name ref="Pertipertus">Pertiperti</name></persName>,
                        alio caput tenet in <rs key="#Landed_possessions #Wood">terra et
                            leccito</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/3308" key="#Confinia">Heriprandi</persName> et
                            <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Teudebrandus">Teoprandi
                            </name></persName>sive <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Gausbertus"
                                >Gosperti</name></persName>, lato uno tenet in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Roads">via et in
                            terra qui fuit <persName ref="#people/3308" key="#Confinia"
                                >Heriprandi</persName></rs>, alio lato tenet in <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >rivo</rs>; suprascripta terra et vinea (…) cum arboribus suis (…).
                        Obbligo: bene laborare et gubernare seu in omnibus meliorare (…). Censo: a
                        parte ipsius episcopatui vestro per singulos annos in ipso loco (…)
                        medietatem vinum purum, quas Dominus exinde donare dignatus fuerit, ad
                        tertiam vices uba legitimas calcata et indi vinata, nam non pondum levandum;
                        et tertiam partem de omni labore, quas Dominus exinde dederit, et super
                        tritura per vindemia super palmentum ibidem misso vestro recipere (…). Pena:
                        argentum soledos quinquaginta. (…). <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name
                                ref="Georgius">Georgius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scrive due <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">cartulas</rs>. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/4" key="#Mother_churches #Bishops">Luca</placeName>.</ab>
                    <ab>Sottoscrivono come <rs key="#Witness">testimoni</rs>: <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Teobaldus">Teopaldo</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Lopo">Lopo</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Alisso">Alisi</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Godesindus">Godesindo</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Deacons"><name ref="Bertaldus"
                            >Bertaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>, <persName><name ref="Eribertus"
                                >Eribertus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name
                                ref="Adroaldus">Atrualdus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>ChLA, 82, n. 43, pp. 146-147; MDL, 5/2, n. 812, p. 493</p>
            </div>
